						<summary>

						<p>Pillar set up near the temple of Ellamma.</p>						

						<p>Telugu Chōḍa: Biji-dēva-Chōḍa Mahārāja.</p>						

						<p>The date portion is damaged and mentions only ba. 1 Thursday.</p>						

						<p>It commences with the <hi rend="italic">‘praśasti’</hi> charaṇa sarōruha etc. It records the gift of the village Bijjāvuram situated in Sakali-dēśa free of all taxes <hi rend="italic">(sarvabādha Parihāram)</hi> by the king to the teacher Uttamaśiva gurudēva. In characters of the 12th century A.D.,</p>						

						</summary>
